  <div class="row" id="query11-div">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/">ETL Facts</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to check the “balance” or the movement of money of a 
        single account by subtracting the sum of all the debit labeled transactions 
        from the sum of all the credit labeled transactions. Since the start date and 
        end date of the transactions is also available, whoever is querying also has the 
        ability to check transactions between two dates such as a certain month or a week.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>
  <!-- Query 1.2 -->
  <br><br>
  <div class="row" id="query12-div">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/">ETL Accounts</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to show the general information about all the transactions 
        of a certain characterization (such as credited interest or insurance payment) per 
        account, like the total amount per account or number of transactions per account. 
        The transactions queried can also be between two specified dates so the user can 
        check transactions for a certain month or week.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

