  <div class="row" id="Count of Credit Card Holders of a Type and Disposition">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/">ETL Time</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to get the total number of card type per disposition 
        type, that is, the query makes use of the Card and Disposition tables to obtain 
        the number of clients who own the following type of cards offered by the Czech 
        bank: Gold, classic, and junior.  Each client, or disposition type, is distinguished 
        by two categories: If they are an owner or a disponent, or someone who uses or is 
        in charge of the card type reflected in the table but does not own it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr>
  <!-- Query 2.2 -->
  <br><br>
  <div class="row" id="Status of Loans and Remaining Balance to be Paid by a Customer">
    <div class="col">
      <a class="query-name" href="/">ETL Recipient</a>
      <p>The purpose of this query is to show if the selected account has any loans. 
        If the account has a loan in record, the details will be displayed. 
        The loan ID, the date the loan was taken, and its current status will be 
        displayed. If the loan is not yet fully paid the remaining balance will be 
        shown by subtracting the transactions made to the loan taken, otherwise it 
        will display that the loan is finished.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

